
{{dated prod|concern = {{{concern|A poorly written page about a useless topic. Should either be deleted or renovated. }}}|month = July|day = 27|year = 2006|time = 14:03|timestamp = 20060727140338}}Judder is an intransitive verb which means to shake and shudder violently. If you have ever let out the clutch in a stopped vehicle without shifting from a high gear back into first gear, and if the vehicle hasn't stalled immediately, you have probably experienced juddering. It is a term most generally used to describe the behavior of machinery in extreme conditions just before failure, but it is also used to describe the behavior of a living creature, such as the scorpion during its mating dance.